# Nuxt 4 Best Practices Guide

## Project Structure (Nuxt 4 Default Structure)

Nuxt 4 introduces a new default project structure, moving all application code to the `app/` directory:

```
.output/
.nuxt/
app/
  assets/
  components/
  composables/
  layouts/
  middleware/
  pages/
  plugins/
  utils/
  app.config.ts
  app.vue
  router.options.ts
content/
layers/
modules/
node_modules/
public/
server/
  api/
  middleware/
  plugins/
  routes/
  utils/
nuxt.config.ts
```

## Directory Structure Best Practices

### 1. Component Organization
- Use nested directories to organize related components: `components/base/foo/Button.vue` → `<BaseFooButton />`
- Use `.client.vue` suffix for client-side only components: `Comments.client.vue`
- Use `.server.vue` suffix for server-side only components: `Comments.server.vue`
- Custom component directory configuration:

```typescript
export default defineNuxtConfig({
  components: [
    // Custom component paths
    { path: '~/calendar-module/components' },
    // Disable path prefix
    { path: '~/user-module/components', pathPrefix: false },
    // Add custom prefix
    { path: '~/components/special-components', prefix: 'Special' },
    '~/components'
  ]
})
```

### 2. Composables Organization
- Top-level files are auto-imported: `composables/useFoo.ts`
- Nested directories need configuration:

```typescript
export default defineNuxtConfig({
  imports: {
    dirs: [
      '~/composables',
      '~/composables/*/index.{ts,js,mjs,mts}',
      '~/composables/**'
    ]
  }
})
```

### 3. Middleware
- Global middleware: `middleware/analytics.global.ts`
- Named middleware: `middleware/auth.ts`
- Execution order control: Use numeric prefixes

```
middleware/
  01.setup.global.ts
  02.analytics.global.ts
  auth.ts
```

### 4. Server Directory
```
server/
  api/
    hello.ts      # /api/v1/hello
  routes/
    bonjour.ts    # /bonjour
  middleware/
    log.ts        # log all requests
```

## Migrating to Nuxt 4

### 1. Maintain Nuxt 3 Structure Configuration
To keep the old directory structure:

```typescript
export default defineNuxtConfig({
  srcDir: '.',
  dir: {
    app: 'app'
  }
})
```

### 2. Run Migration Tool
```bash
npx codemod@latest nuxt/4/migration-recipe
```

### 3. Configuration Migration
- `generate` → `nitro.prerender`
- `build.publicPath` → `app.cdnURL`
- `router.base` → `app.baseURL`

```typescript
export default defineNuxtConfig({
  nitro: {
    prerender: {
      ignore: ['/admin', '/private'],
      routes: ['/sitemap.xml', '/robots.txt']
    }
  },
  app: {
    cdnURL: 'https://my-cdn.net',
    baseURL: '/my-app/'
  }
})
```

## API Best Practices

### 1. Data Fetching
Use `useLazyFetch` instead of `useFetch` for better performance:

```typescript
// Recommended
const { data: posts } = useLazyFetch('/api/v1/posts')

// useFetch defaults to shallow reactivity in Nuxt 4
const { data } = useFetch('/api/v1/test', { deep: true })
```

### 2. Component Auto-import
Component naming convention is now standardized:
- `components/SomeFolder/MyComponent.vue` → `<SomeFolderMyComponent />`

### 3. Experimental Features Configuration
```typescript
export default defineNuxtConfig({
  experimental: {
    viewTransition: true,
    asyncContext: true,
    appManifest: true
  }
})
```

## Performance Optimization

### 1. Build Optimization
```typescript
export default defineNuxtConfig({
  vite: {
    build: {
      assetsDir: '_nuxt/'
    }
  },
  nitro: {
    experimental: {
      wasm: true
    }
  }
})
```

### 2. Type Safety
```typescript
export default defineNuxtConfig({
  typescript: {
    strict: true,
    typeCheck: true
  }
})
```

## Development Tools Configuration

### 1. DevTools
```typescript
export default defineNuxtConfig({
  devtools: { enabled: true }
})
```

### 2. Debug Mode
```typescript
export default defineNuxtConfig({
  debug: process.env.NODE_ENV === 'development'
})
```

## File Naming Conventions

- Pages: `pages/index.vue`, `pages/[id].vue`
- Layouts: `layouts/default.vue`, `layouts/custom.vue`
- Components: `components/AppHeader.vue`
- Middleware: `middleware/auth.ts`
- Plugins: `plugins/foo.ts`
- Composables: `composables/useAuth.ts`
- Utils: `utils/helpers.ts`

## Shared Directory

Nuxt 4 introduces the `shared/` directory for client and server shared code:

```
shared/
  utils/
    lower.ts           # Auto-imported
  types/
    bar.d.ts           # Auto-imported
  capitalize.ts        # Not auto-imported
  formatters/
    upper.ts           # Not auto-imported
```

## Layers Usage

For complex projects, use Nuxt Layers:

```
some-app/
  nuxt.config.ts
  pages/
    app-page.vue
nuxt.config.ts
```

```typescript
export default defineNuxtConfig({
  extends: ['./some-app']
})
```




















